org.jlinalg.fastrational

Class FastRationalFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jlinalg.RingElementFactory<FastRational>
      • org.jlinalg.fastrational.FastRationalFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, IRingElementFactory<FastRational>

    public class FastRationalFactory
extends RingElementFactory<FastRational>
    An implementation of rational numbers based on long numbers in order to improve the memory footprint and calculation time as compared to Rational.

    This, however, comes at a price: if the numerator or denominator leaves the domain of long-numbers, results will be wrong (no test for overflows is performed).

    Author:
    Georg Thimm
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • get

        public FastRational get(java.lang.Object object)
        Translate other objects into FastRationals. Objects in the following classes are permissible:
        • those extending on Number,
        • Rational,
        • DoubleWrapper
        • String in the form of integers, exponential or fractional representation.
        If the argument is a FastRational, it is returned. Should the given object exceed the range of long numbers, the result is silently truncated.
        Specified by:
        get in interface IRingElementFactory<FastRational>
        Overrides:
        get in class RingElementFactory<FastRational>
        Parameters:
        object -
        Returns:
        the corresponding object of type RE
        Throws:
        InvalidOperationException - if object is not in one of the given classes and object.toString() is in an unknown format.
        See Also:
        IRingElementFactory.get(java.lang.Object)
